The paper proposes a novel hierarchical Bayesian deep auto-encoder model for factor disentanglement, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the use of long-tail distributions and Gaussian priors, which are concepts commonly used in deep learning and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SD (Sound).
